# Build output metadata (agent)

## Required layout (`bin/win/current`)

After any exe deploy, `bin/win/current` must contain this engineering set:

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `EraseAndRewrite.exe` | Shipping binary |
| `versioninfo.json` | Canonical four-part version; copied from `win-cpp-qt/versioninfo.json` |
| `build-meta.json` | Trace: `productVersion`, `build`, `buildPadded`, `folderStem`, `branch`, `commit`, `commitShort`, `timeUtc` |
| `*.date` | Archive stem; `Prepare-CurrentBuildFolder` moves `current` into `bin/win/<stem>/` on the next build |

Without the `.date` marker, the next `build.ps1` run wipes `current` instead of archiving it.

`win-cpp-qt/build.ps1` writes metadata immediately after exe deploy/strip and before `test-run.ps1`. `Test-BuildOutputMetadata` and `test-run.ps1` fail if any piece is missing.

Interrupted deploy (exe only): `powershell -File win-cpp-qt/tools/restore-build-metadata.ps1`

## Installer exclusion (mandatory)

`installer/Erase & Rewrite.iss` `[Files]` is an explicit allow-list:

- `EraseAndRewrite.exe` from `SourceDir`
- `COPYING`, `LICENSE-NOTICE`, `THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES` from `installer/`

Never add wildcards over `SourceDir`. Never install `versioninfo.json`, `build-meta.json`, or `*.date` to `{app}` (legalspec LS-123, build-workflow §3).

`SourceDir` is usually `bin/win/current`, which legitimately contains metadata beside the exe; the installer ignores them by design.

## Agent obligations (when Mutabor authorizes build)

1. Prefer `win-cpp-qt/build.ps1 -StaticQt` so metadata is written and validated automatically.
2. Do not leave `bin/win/current` with only an exe.
3. Read `build-meta.json` and `versioninfo.json` before claiming a build number or commit.
4. Do not add metadata files to installer `[Files]` or copy them into `{app}`.
